processed_text: Mr. Wolff, I commend you and I want to thank you for your education regarding the problems and how to resolve the problems of the Capitalist system and that it should be transformed not attempted to be fixed, since the system itself is the problem. Now, having said that, I do not agree with you comment to the Chinese gentleman, when you said that China will suffer the same issues due to it allowing the Capitalists to come over and succeed in China. The reasons that I do not agree with your analysis are that in the Capitalist system it is the economic system, meaning the rich, who own the economy, will decide the political agenda, the rues and laws on how things will be, regarding the wealth distribution and how the lives of the people will be shaped as a result of that. The rich are the ones who own the economy and bankroll the politicians that are elected, and in turn the politicians will cater to the needs of the rich and rich only. In the Communist system, it is the government which decides how the economy will be and in the Communist system, the people are taken care of first and foremost, taken care that they will be educated, provided with health care and all of the necessities of what people need to live a comfortable worry free life, provided with the needed services at the lowest cost and in some cases for free, before anything else, unlike the Capitalist system, where everything costs and costs a lot, as you are well aware of. So if a Capitalist, for example, moves his cell phone making factory or whatever factory he has, to China to cut down our costs, you can be guaranteed that the Chinese person producing these cell phone or whatever else they produce, will be able to buy these products at the cost that he or she is producing these products, the Capitalist can take these cell phones and sell them in the U.S. or Germany or wherever he wants to sell these phones at, at whatever price he wants to sell them at, but in China he will sell them at the cost that they are produced, because the Chinese government will make sure that their own people will be able to buy these products that they produce and not be taken advantage of by these Capitalists. The reason that the Capitalists move their factories to China is not only because the low cost of labour but also because the working force is much more organized, educated and larger than anywhere else in the world. So your claim that China will suffer the same as the U.S. or any other capitalist country suffers because of the Capitalist system, is not true, because the Chinese communist government will first and foremost take care of the needs of its own people. As far as the billionaires in China, you can be sure that they pay more taxes than the average Chinese person, as it should be, and you can be sure that no Chinese person suffers because of the wealth of these billionaires, since there is no exploitation of the working force as we see in the western capitalist countries.I would like to hear what your response to my post is and if you can, please email me at: moshe.roseshter@gmail.com.

author: @BritishArmyTributes
processed_text: I have heard Dr Walker cover naps but it was somewhat brief. He said that biphasic sleeping is practised within some older tribal communities and involves around 7 hours of sleep during the night, followed by a nap later on in the afternoon. He speaks of a hardwired, evolutionary dip productivity in humans between 2-4pm. This happens, he says, regardless of whether a large lunch was consumed, regardless of the person's diet, wellbeing and regardless of whether or not optimal sleep was achieved that night. He recommends that naps, while good if kept on the shorter side, should not be taken if you are someone who has issues achieving good quality, uninterrupted sleep during the night. If you sleep just fine during the night, then naps should be of no detrimentWith regards to audio, he did some videos for Penguin Books UK here on YT. One of the questions he answered was whether white noise/ocean sounds etc can assist with sleep. He said while there are no concrete findings on this yet, one of his theories was that non invasive tones played during sleep (sounds that can be played but that won't wake you) could sync up with the brain wave fluctuations we experience in different stages of our sleep. If this was true, it could mean that a deeper deep sleep could be reached through the use of rhythmic or repetitive tones or sounds. The video explains it better than I can, haha

author: @randominternetcommenter7595
processed_text: IMO, his conclusions are not very well supported at all.  At 10:25 he says nuclear and hydro are the best ways to combat climate change.  The problem is that nuclear power costs 3 to 5 times other clean energy sources and also it can't economically adjust its output to follow load, which  is a requirement if you want to use a single generation source to meet all your power needs. Wind and solar aren't perfect because their output is intermittent. However, they're really really cheap compared to nuclear.  In the short term, by far the cheapest approach is to pair wind and solar with hydro and natural gas and maybe some batteries as their cost comes down.  In the long term, most energy experts expect solar and wind to get paired with hydrogen powered generation, with the hydrogen fuel created and stored when there's an excess of wind and solar power.

对科技东西。我真是看不懂李辉林+知青大叔二 其实最科学的就是最客观普遍存在的。1、汽车运动理论，是在固定动力能量范围内，靠调整其驱动力与驱动速度地相互转换关系、来适应客观环境条件地行驶。可中国伪动力科学理论却是：靠增加动力（如同更换不同的发动机）的能量大小（倍量差），去完成实现比别人高百分之几的“国际领先”地速度。2、不要被“宇宙物质结构动力能量学”（演变论）的无穷大理论给搞蒙了，宇宙中所有的物质都是由正（质子、中子）负（电子）物质及能量、结构、运动、变化所组成的（就像电子计算机仅仅只是地球人依靠利用了自然界中，最微小一部分的电子地得失：“1”与“0”这宇宙最简单普遍的物质关系及变化规律，就可以计算、记录、模仿、设计出最为复杂的事物与客观自然世界现象。）。现实科学理论认为：物质具有“万有引力”，所以电子围绕质子中子转、月亮围绕地球转、地球围绕太阳转动、、、、、、！那么物质如果只存在万有引力，电子就会被原子核吸引在一起、月亮就会被地球吸引在引起、地球当然也要被太阳吸引在一起，整个宇宙中所有的物质不都会被吸引成一个没有任何空间运动的奇点？所以这个“万有引力理论”是不客观完善的，必须存在一个与之抗衡、互补、共存的“万有斥力”，才会将宇宙物质激活、运动、展开成现实的样子。我的创新动力学理论就是这样从发现、现实的应用动力学理论的“力不平衡”现象中，发现了人类基础物理理论的不足之处，而提出了可以包罗整个宇宙更为客观、普遍、可证地理论基础。是不论有无所谓专业科学知识的都能了解认识的，就像当年人们了解认识牛顿提出的“苹果落地”一样，只是在他的认识上更客观完善了。当然对于搞更专业深入的分枝，是必须要有专业知识才能进行的，就像轮船、飞机、火箭同属于动力学分枝，需要不同的专业人员，但是他们一定是在同一个共同地动力学理论基础上展开发展的。即使《相对论》提出了“不同参照系”的认识论，但是在对动力物理的认识上，是继续了其“物质运动能量不平衡”地不足的。希望能够像“苹果落地”样能够被认识接受。只是苹果落地时、怎么没有出现“万有斥力”（与两物体的质量成正比，与两物体间的距离成反比，方向相反、呈离心力。）？那是因为与地球的万有引力比，苹果的万有斥力太小太弱，它不是月亮，完全被忽略不计。同理、如果在月亮的位置上只是一只苹果，因为其质量太小、与地球的距离又太远，地球对它地“万有引力”（与两物体的质量成正比，与两物体间的距离成反比，方向相同、呈向心力。）也就弱小得忽略不计，只能认其在太空自由中翱游。（2016年2月26日）

author: @Stevehtegreatgr
processed_text: This is easily his most controversial statement. In biology organisms are thought as systems. Systems are very different than algorithms. They are made by algorithms but when those algorithms work in unison or in teams they produce different results than if they simply worked alone. In other words new unexpected properties arise in systems that are not predicted by the algorithms themselves. This feature of systems is called "emergence" and is pretty much why organisms are NOT algorithms, a bit of how a forest is not just a bunch of trees, it's a bunch of trees working together in a manner different than if they were as numerous get geographically displaced from one another.To explain a system you can't just explain the underlying algorithm, you should also explain how they interact together, in other words the emergent properties of the system and then you have something concrete to work with. Saying organisms are algorithms implies knowing how every algorithm individualy works would also give us how the organism works , which is nonsense. This is 19th CE reductionism.Organisms are NOT algorithms. Organisms are complex systems made from algorithms.

processed_text: WARNING ! HIGH RISK OF P-HACKING !!! Both implicit or explicit p-hacking.This type of Studies are of course interesting in principle, BUT, have a low sample size,  plus most importantly the researchers ( in general) have no incentive to present , openly show ALL the data and failed or semi failed experiments. author: @Madsy9
processed_text: Thomas McCabe You can "hack" the blockchain if you control over half of the network which validates the transactions. One might brush off such an attack as unfeasible or unlikely, but it is a potential attack vector and the probability of it being abused grows every day. Some of the largest miner groups have controlled such a large portion of the transactions at peak times by accident. Fortunately for everyone they had no nefarious intentions. There is also the issue that bitcoins are finite in quantity and that bitcoins are literally lost when people forget the password to their wallets or the wallet is lost. While bitcoins can be split up into really small fractions to mitigate this somewhat, this phenomenon might end up making a few individuals very rich, or bitcoins essentially worthless over time.Also to answer your other point, even when you do transactions with companies and people you trust, disagreements and disputes do occur. It doesn't necessarily mean that either party is deliberately trying to fraud the other. There are advantages of having chargebacks just like there are good arguments for a non-regulated currency system.Like all currencies, Bitcoin has some advantages and some disadvantages. If people want Bitcoin to become more popular and easier to use, we should at least be honest about the possible challenges with the system.

author: @WalkAwayaFreeMan
processed_text: Hey, Kentucky, On some level I think I can understand why you feel so strongly about access to abortion that you would say that (assuming you are opposed to the message in this video). Can I ask if you have ever tried to put yourself in the shoes of those whose opinion you oppose? People on the other side genuinely believe that there are millions of innocent children's lives in the balance. What would you do and how would you feel if you genuinely believed a child's life was in danger in the room next-door to you? Can you see how this issue is different from slavery? Pimps and terrorists dehumanize other people so they can treat them as property. That's what makes supporters of slavery guilty of hate speech. By contrast, those who take the pro-life position seek to humanize those whom they believe are already being dehumanized. That's why they view their position as a matter of love.At the same time, I have friends who support abortion who also believe their position is a matter of love. Wouldn't you agree that two sides who believe they are fighting for love should seek to have conversation with one another instead of taking up arms against one another? If two people who believe in love cannot discuss their differences, then what is the point of a multicultural society? It is one thing to silence those who espouse hate (dehumanization a la slavery, racial supremacism, ethnic cleansing, etc.), but another thing entirely to silence those who genuinely believe they are seeking to love. Those of us who belong to the second group have to protect our ability to talk to one another! Otherwise our civilization will become a dictatorship.Thanks for considering what I have to say, Kentucky. I'd be happy to hear any other thoughts you might have in response?All the best,Christopher
